1. Convert a Tuple t = (1,2,3,4,5) to a list

t=(1,2,3,4,5)
l=list(t)
print(l)

O/P

[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

2.WAP to join a list and a tuple:L = [1,3,5,7] T = (8,6,4,2) 

l = [1,3,5,7] 
t = (8,6,4,2)
l.extend(t)
ls=l
print(ls)

O/P

[1, 3, 5, 7, 8, 6, 4, 2]

Q.3 List and Tuple Diff-:

List is mutable 
Tuple is immutable 

Q.4 Print the list in reverse order -: l = [‘a’, ‘d’, ‘c’, ‘A’, ‘C’]

l=['a','d','c','A','C']

print(l[::-1])

Q.5:Print Elements at Odd indexes from a list (Do not use loop)l = [10,11,20, 21,30, 31, 40, 41]

import random
l=[10,11,20, 21,30, 31, 40, 41]
a=l[1:8:2]
print(a)

O/p-:
[11, 21, 31, 41]


